<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 30 at 4:59AM CDT until March 30 at 5:30AM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 530 AM CDT
FOR NORTHERN LAMAR AND EASTERN FANNIN COUNTIES...
At 458 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles northwest
of Paris, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Honey Grove, Roxton, Ladonia, Windom and Toco.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for north central
Texas.</instruction>
